docs.summary:
Retrieves a list of OAuth apps, given the provided paging, filtering, and sorting.


Query OAuth Apps runs with these defaults, which you can override:
+ Results are sorted by `id` in descending order.
+ `paging.offset` is `0`.

For field support for filters and sorting, see [OAuth Apps: Supported Filters and Sorting](https://dev.wix.com/api/rest/auth-management/oauth-apps/filters-&-sorting)

To learn about working with _Query_ endpoints in general, see [API Query Language](https://dev.wix.com/api/rest/getting-started/api-query-language).

docs.summary: An intermediary application that authorizes and authenticates an external client to access data on a Wix project or site.

members.name: id
members.doc: ID of the OAuth app.

members.name: createdDate
members.doc: Date and time the OAuth app was created, in ISO 8601 format.

members.name: name
members.doc: Display name of the OAuth app, as it appears in the dashboard.

members.name: description
members.doc: Description of the OAuth app, as it appears in the dashboard.

members.name: secret
members.doc: For internal use only.

members.name: loginUrl
members.doc: External login URL to which users are redirected automatically to authenticate. If no login URL is specified, the user is redirected to Wix to authenticate.

members.name: allowedRedirectUris
members.doc:
List of URIs to which redirection from Wix is allowed after authentication.

 When a client redirects a user to Wix for authentication, the client provides a URI to redirect the user back to after the user has been authenticated.
 Wix only redirects the user if the exact URI is contained in this array.

members.name: allowedRedirectDomains
members.doc:
List of domains to which redirection from Wix is allowed after processes other than authentication.

 When a client redirects a user to a Wix page (for example, for checkout), the client provides a URL to redirect the user back to.
 Wix only redirects the user if the URL is in one of the specified domains.

members.name: allowSecretGeneration
members.doc:
Whether a secret can be generated for this OAuth app.

 Default: `true` until a secret has been generated for the OAuth App.

members.name: logoutUrl
members.doc: External logout URL to which we invoke when user logout at wix. If no logout URL is specified, the user is logged out only at Wix.

members.name: paths
members.doc: The set of field mask paths.

members.name: limit
members.doc: Number of items to load.

members.name: offset
members.doc: Number of items to skip in the current sort order.

members.name: limit
members.doc: Maximum number of items to return in the results.

members.name: cursor
members.doc:
Pointer to the next or previous page in the list of results.

Pass the relevant cursor token from the `pagingMetadata` object in the previous call's response.
Not relevant for the first request.

members.name: count
members.doc: Number of items returned in the response.

members.name: offset
members.doc: Offset that was requested.

members.name: total
members.doc: Total number of items that match the query. Returned if offset paging is used and the `tooManyToCount` flag is not set.

members.name: tooManyToCount
members.doc: Flag that indicates the server failed to calculate the `total` field.

members.name: cursors
members.doc: Cursors to navigate through the result pages using `next` and `prev`. Returned if cursor paging is used.

members.name: next
members.doc: Cursor string pointing to the next page in the list of results.

members.name: prev
members.doc: Cursor pointing to the previous page in the list of results.

members.name: fieldName
members.doc: Name of the field to sort by.

members.name: order
members.doc: Sort order.

members.name: filter
sort
members.doc:
Sort object in the following format:
`[{"fieldName":"name","order":"ASC"},{"fieldName":"created_date","order":"DESC"}]`

members.name: paging
members.doc: Paging options to limit and skip the number of items.

members.name: cursorPaging
members.doc: Cursor token pointing to a page of results. Not used in the first request. Following requests use the cursor token and not `filter` or `sort`.

docs.summary:
Possible values are:
  • ASC
  • DESC

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN
  • ENABLED
  • DISABLED
  • PENDING
  • DEMO

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN
  • TRASH
  • DELETED
  • PENDING_PURGE

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN_NAMESPACE
  • WIX - Default namespace for UGC sites. MetaSites with this namespace will be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • SHOUT_OUT - ShoutOut stand alone product. These are siteless (no actual Wix site, no HtmlWeb). MetaSites with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • ALBUMS - MetaSites created by the Albums product, they appear as part of the Albums app. MetaSites with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • WIX_STORES_TEST_DRIVE - Part of the WixStores migration flow, a user tries to migrate and gets this site to view and if the user likes it then stores removes this namespace and deletes the old site with the old stores. MetaSites with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • HOTELS - Hotels standalone (siteless). MetaSites with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • CLUBS - Clubs siteless MetaSites, a club without a wix website. MetaSites with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • ONBOARDING_DRAFT - A partially created ADI website. MetaSites with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • DEV_SITE - AppBuilder for AppStudio / shmite (c). MetaSites with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • LOGOS - LogoMaker websites offered to the user after logo purchase. MetaSites with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • VIDEO_MAKER - VideoMaker websites offered to the user after video purchase. MetaSites with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • PARTNER_DASHBOARD - MetaSites with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • DEV_CENTER_COMPANY - MetaSites with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • HTML_DRAFT - A draft created by HTML editor on open. Upon "first save" it will be moved to be of WIX domain. Meta site with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • SITELESS_BUSINESS - the user-journey for Fitness users who want to start from managing their business instead of designing their website. Will be accessible from Site List and will not have a website app. Once the user attaches a site, the site will become a regular wixsite.
  • CREATOR_ECONOMY - Belongs to "strategic products" company. Supports new product in the creator's economy space.
  • DASHBOARD_FIRST - * It is to be used in the Business First efforts.
  • ANYWHERE - * Bookings business flow with no site.
  • HEADLESS - * Namespace for Headless Backoffice with no editor
  • ACCOUNT_MASTER_CMS - * Namespace for master site that will exist in parent account that will be referenced by subaccounts The site will be used for account level CSM feature for enterprise
  • RISE - * Rise.ai Siteless account management for Gift Cards and Store Credit.
  • BRANDED_FIRST - * As part of the branded app new funnel, users now can create a meta site that will be branded app first. There's a blank site behind the scene but it's blank). The Mobile company will be the owner of this namespace.

Possible values are:
  • OTHER - A valid option, we don't expose all reasons why site might be created.
  • FROM_TEMPLATE - A meta site was created from template.
  • DUPLICATE_BY_SITE_TRANSFER - A meta site was created by copying of the transfferred meta site.
  • DUPLICATE - A copy of existing meta site.
  • OLD_SITE_TRANSFER - A meta site was created as a transfferred site (copy of the original), old flow, should die soon.
  • FLASH - deprecated A meta site was created for Flash editor.
